{
  "texts": [
    "We instantiate BTL2 within the framework of Section 4.3 as follows.",
    "Let ϕ(e 1), ϕ(e 2) ∈ R d be the embeddings of base judge's rationales e 1 and e 2, respectively; and b 1, b 2 > 0 be the associated scores.",
    "We define the probability that the first response is preferred as (3), where ϕ(e) = ϕ(e 1) -ϕ(e 2) and p = b 1 /(b 1 + b 2).",
    "This representation is motivated by the fact that the difference of the embeddings ϕ(e) = ϕ(e 1) -ϕ(e 2) reflects the difference of word affinities in the two responses.",
    "The probability p biases the response towards the base judge."
  ]
}